
- fish photo shooting: 
	- gPhoto: libgphoto2 supports eos 600D
		- gphoto2 
			--camera="Canon EOS 600D" 
			--capture-image-and-download 
			--filename=asd 
			--no-keep
		- auto-Abschalten deaktivieren. Sonst disconnected sie usb 

- fish photo processing: ("scanner")
	- Verworfen: 
		- python + pillow => PIL.Image.composite
		- then transform to 1024x1024 png
	- Stattdessen: 
		- in Rust, geht gut. 
		- Erlaube variablen Fisch-umriss durch background removal

- load into fish styler (web app, executes "take photo", shows foto, "select background color", executes rust script, moves folder to "sea" program)
	- appearance: 
		- skin color
		- all axis scale
		- surface constant [has to equal] pow(size,2) * amount
	- behaviour
		- swarm factor 
	- Ok saves it to the aquarium fish folder

- Drop them into the sea
	- particle data buffer
		- device local
	- compute particle update
		- in
			- flux
			- particle data 
				- speed
				- position
				- swarm_offset
			- species data 
		- out
			- updated particle data
			- vertex data 
	- Pro Spezies: 
		- Partikel Buffer
		- Vertex Buffer
		- Draw Call 
		- (vielleicht sogar ein eigenes noise... Aber cooler w√§re wahrscheinlich ein globales noise + dann noch ein offset und drift auf Spezies-ebene ;)				
